step_data.thought: The user wants to know the maximum area size that can be exported from OpenStreetMap. On the export page, the page indicates that the selected area is too large to be exported as OpenStreetMap XML Data. The area provided is a bounding box from -74.4193, 40.3361 to -73.7807, 41.0571. The page suggests using other sources for downloading this large area. I will provide this information to the user.
step_data.action: stop('The selected area is too large to be exported as OpenStreetMap XML Data. The bounding box provided is from -74.4193, 40.3361 to -73.7807, 41.0571. You can use other sources such as Overpass API, Planet OSM, Geofabrik Downloads, or Other Sources listed on the OpenStreetMap Wiki to download this large area.')
